      "order": 1,
      "Description": "This lesson explores how malicious actors can attempt to steal or replicate proprietary machine learning models without authorisation. You will learn about the key techniques attackers use, including model extraction attacks, where repeated queries are used to reconstruct a model's behaviour and capabilities. The lesson also covers why these risks matter for organisations that have invested significant resources in developing and training their models. By the end, you will have a clearer understanding of the potential vulnerabilities involved and the practical steps that can be taken to reduce exposure to these threats.",
