          "subtitle": "Mapping the methods attackers commonly exploit",
          "slidecontent": "• Repeated querying of a model's outputs to reverse-engineer its internal logic and decision boundaries\n• Training a smaller \"student\" model to mimic the behaviour of a target model using stolen predictions\n• Membership inference attacks, which probe whether specific data was used during training\n• Side-channel attacks exploiting timing or resource usage patterns\n• Scraping publicly exposed API endpoints at scale to harvest enough responses for reconstruction\n• Gradient leakage, where shared updates in federated learning inadvertently reveal private model parameters"
